description.narrative: Honduras approved the National Action Plan for the Response to Violence against Children.Considering all UNICEF interventions, 226,152 children who suffered violence received health, social services or protection support, including preventive actions.Municipalities protected more than 12,000 children through 266 safe spaces and continued to provide medical, legal and victim support services. With support from UNICEF, the government launched awareness campaigns to reduce violence, reaching more than 180,000 people. The 110 helpline was created to report violence and provide counselling and psychological first aid and the first government website to inform children about violence prevention was launched. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:27/01/2022
